history.content:
<md>I was planning out my schedule for EECS and it says that I need a technical elective from "Lower or upper div 4 units in Astro, Chem, Data Sci, EPS, IB, Math, MCB, Physics, PMB, Stat, or any Engin┼ dept."

I took and received qualifying scores in both AP and IB Biology, as well as AP Chemistry. Can I use AP Biology credit for the natural science fulfilment and AP Chemistry as a technical elective? This AP Chemistry gives me credit for CHEM 1A + 1AL, which is in the Chem department in the technical elective section.</md>
history.subject: Can technical elective for EECS be an AP credit?
